All these commands need to be run on the FNAL gpvms.

To build/link all the event generators and NUISANCE:

git clone https://github.com/afropapp13/BuildEventGenerators.git;
cd BuildEventGenerators;
./build_generators.sh;

To test that the build was successful by producing a few events:

cd example;
./run_all.sh;

To set up the environment, source the setup script every time you connect to the gpvm machines:

source setup_generators.sh

GENIE cross-section splines

Generate a GENIE spline XML with gmkspl before running gevgen if the required probe/target/interaction/tune/energy-range combination is not already available:

gmkspl -p 14 -t 1000180400 -e 10. \
  -o example/samples/14_1000180400_CC_v3_6_2_AR23_20i_00_000.xml \
  --tune AR23_20i_00_000 --event-generator-list CC

This example is for numu (PDG 14) charged-current scattering on Ar-40 (1000180400) using tune AR23_20i_00_000 up to 10 GeV. The flux file is not an input to gmkspl; it is supplied later to gevgen with -f flux.root,histname. Regenerate the XML only when the probe, target, interaction list, GENIE tune/model setup, or energy coverage changes.
